State-owned &lt;Chemie Linz AG> islikely to record a 1986 loss of some 600 mln schillingscompared with a 340 mln loss in 1985, a company spokesman said.    Falling sales and lower world prices of fertilisers werelargely responsible for the sharp increase, along with theeffects of the dollar's fall which has helped to give U.S.Fibre producers a competitive edge, he told Reuters.    The firm would have made a small profit in 1985 had it notbeen for 456 mln schillings lost by subsidiary &lt;MerxHandelsgesmbH> on oil trading. Merx has since withdrawn fromthe oil market. The firm will announce 1986 results in July. Reuter&#3;